column1: text
Machine learning algorithms include supervised and unsupervised learning. Neural networks are a key component of deep learning.
Python programming basics include variables, functions, classes, and object-oriented programming concepts.
Data structures such as arrays, linked lists, stacks, and queues are fundamental to computer science.
Web development involves HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks like React and Angular.
Database management includes SQL queries, normalization, indexing, and relational database design.
Computer networks cover TCP/IP protocols, routing, switching, and network security.
Operating systems manage processes, threads, memory, and file systems.
Software engineering principles include design patterns, testing, debugging, and version control.
Statistics and probability are essential for data analysis and machine learning.
Linear algebra concepts like vectors, matrices, and eigenvalues are used in machine learning.
Calculus including derivatives and integrals is important for understanding optimization algorithms.
Discrete mathematics covers logic, sets, graphs, and combinatorial problems.
Computer architecture includes CPU design, memory hierarchy, and instruction sets.
Cryptography involves encryption, decryption, and secure communication protocols.
Human-computer interaction focuses on user interface design and usability.
Ethics in technology covers privacy, bias in AI, and responsible innovation.
Cloud computing provides scalable infrastructure and services like AWS and Azure.
DevOps combines development and operations for continuous integration and deployment.
Blockchain technology enables decentralized and secure transaction systems.
Internet of Things connects physical devices to the internet for smart applications.
